	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Of course you can do this, I already explained on the <a href="http://nesdevwiki.org/wiki/index.php/SNROM" class="postlink">Wiki</a> how to do that. You basically just have to add resistory and dides where there is slot for, and remove the solder shorting D2 (the pas seems named 'SL' on SNROM-04 and higher, but have no name in SNROM-03 and lower).
<br />
<br />If you add a battery to Cool Spot, this will have absolutely no effect : The SRAM data will be preserved but the game didn't except it to be preserved so nothing special will hapen. However, you can put another game on place of the mask rom and do this. If your weird japanese Zelda has no battery, you can do this too.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
